OL,4,CRicher parents pressured teachers on
OL,5,Cexam grades
OL,6, Parents of pupils in private schools or
OL,7, living in affluent areas of England
OL,8, were the most likely to put pressure on
OL,9, teachers over exam grades, suggests
OL,10, research from the Sutton Trust.
OL,12,FAlmost a quarter of private school
OL,13,Fteachers had been contacted by parents
OL,14,Fover A-level and GCSE grades, twice as
OL,15,Fmany as in schools in deprived areas.
OL,17,FTeachers submitted grades this year
OL,18,Fafter exams were disrupted by Covid.
OL,20,FHead teachers warned such lobbying was
OL,21,F"inappropriate" and added stress.
